to apply a deployment 

kubectl apply -f deployment.yaml 
deployment.apps/nginx-deployment created

2.	List all available Deployments

kubectl get deployments
	NAME               READY   UP-TO-DATE   AVAILABLE   AGE
nginx-deployment   1/1     1            1           30s

3.	Describe the Deployment to view detailed info

kubectl describe deployments nginx-deployment kubectl describe deployments nginx-deployment 

	4.	Scale the Deployment to a different number of Pods
kubectl scale deployment nginx-deployment --replicas 4
deployment.apps/nginx-deployment scaled

5- delete the Deployment
kubectl delete deployment nginx-deployment